.TH GUIX "1" "January 2026" "GNU" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
guix \- manual page for guix repl (GNU Guix) 1.5.0rc1.47-fc2f5a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B guix
\fI\,repl \/\fR[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR...] [\fI\,-- FILE ARGS\/\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
In the Guix execution environment, run FILE as a Guile script with
command\-line arguments ARGS.  If no FILE is given, start a Guile REPL.
.TP
\fB\-\-list\-types\fR
display REPL types and exit
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-type\fR=\fI\,TYPE\/\fR
start a REPL of the given TYPE
.TP
\fB\-\-listen\fR=\fI\,ENDPOINT\/\fR
listen to ENDPOINT instead of standard input
.TP
\fB\-q\fR
inhibit loading of ~/.guile
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-interactive\fR
launch REPL after evaluating FILE
.TP
\fB\-L\fR, \fB\-\-load\-path\fR=\fI\,DIR\/\fR
prepend DIR to the package module search path
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
display this help and exit
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
display version information and exit
